# WOLF3D – AI-Assisted Retro Porting Lab licensing

## Original project work: CC0-1.0

To the extent that [@iz2rpn](https://github.com/iz2rpn) and WOLF3D lab
contributors own the copyright and related rights, the original work created
for this project is dedicated to the public domain under **CC0 1.0 Universal**.

You may copy, modify, distribute, study, teach from, and use that original work
for any purpose, including commercial purposes, without asking permission.

This dedication covers the original WOLF3D lab tooling, tests, Codex skill,
configuration, scripts, reports, benchmarks, documentation, and Z6S adapter
code, except where a file or the path rules below identify upstream-derived or
third-party material.

The complete CC0 legal text is in `LICENSES/CC0-1.0.txt`; the canonical source
is https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/.

## Upstream-derived paths

The author cannot waive rights owned by other people. These narrow paths retain
the license of the source they modify:

| Path | Governing license |
|---|---|
| `patches/wolf4sdl-z6s.patch` | GPL-2.0-only path selected from Wolf4SDL's included licensing options |
| `patches/wolf4sdl-z6s-native-video.patch` | GPL-2.0-only path selected from Wolf4SDL's included licensing options |
| `patches/sdl12-z6s.patch` | LGPL-2.1-or-later, matching SDL 1.2 |
| `patches/tinyalsa-no-plugins.patch` | BSD-3-Clause, matching tinyalsa |

Corresponding license texts are stored under `LICENSES/`. Upstream source is
not vendored; `scripts/fetch_sources.sh` obtains exact commits with their own
notices.

The original Z6S adapter source is offered under CC0 as a standalone
contribution. A compiled binary that combines it with GPL-covered Wolf4SDL must
still comply with the GPL and all other linked-component obligations.

## Excluded rights and assets

CC0 does not grant rights to Wolfenstein 3D game data, trademarks, id Software
code under its historical license, vendor firmware/UI files, recovered
binaries, personal device data, or any other third-party work. Those materials
are not included in the public repository.

See `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md` for the dependency and asset boundary. This mapping
documents the repository policy; it is not legal advice.
